A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO THE UNIVERSITY OF HAWAII.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. Section 304A-2153, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by amending subsection (b) to read as follows:
3 "(b) Any law to the contrary notwithstanding, the board of
4 regents may authorize expenditures of up to $3,000,000 annually,
5 excluding in-kind services, from this fund for the purposes of
6 promoting alumni relations, conducting donor evaluations, and
7 generating private donations for deposit into the University of
8 Hawaii Foundation for the purposes of the university. Any
9 expenditure authorized pursuant to this subsection shall be for
10 a public purpose and shall not be subject to chapters 42F, 103,
11 103D, and 103F. The university shall submit a comprehensive
12 report to the legislature detailing the use of any funds
13 authorized by the board under this subsection no later than
14 twenty days prior to the convening of each regular session.
15 The report shall:
16 (1) Identify each department of the University of Hawaii
17 Foundation supported by moneys from the fund;
